Title: The Last Transmission
Author: Storyboard AI Demo
Draft date: July 3, 2026
Format: Fountain
Credit: Written by
Contact: demo@storyboardai.com

FADE IN:

INT. DEEP SPACE RELAY STATION — NIGHT

Darkness, broken only by the blue pulse of standby monitors. A
single EMERGENCY LIGHT revolves slowly, casting blood-red arcs
across walls lined with dormant equipment.

DR. YAEL OKAFOR (50s, silver-streaked hair, exhaustion carved into
every line of her face) sits at the primary array console. Coffee
gone cold beside her. Headset clamped on.

She listens. Static. Only static.

YAEL
(to herself)
Come on. Fourteen months. You
have to be out there.

She adjusts the frequency. The static shifts — almost musical.

YAEL (CONT'D)
(bolt upright)
There.

EXT. RELAY STATION — CONTINUOUS

The great dish arrays tilt in unison, all eighteen of them,
pivoting toward the same point in the darkness — a specific patch
of empty sky between the stars.

INT. DEEP SPACE RELAY STATION — CONTINUOUS

The monitors wake. Data cascades. Yael's hands fly across the
console.

YAEL
Recording. All channels. Do not
interrupt me.

Behind her, LIEUTENANT CROSS (30s, regulation haircut, skeptic's
eyes) steps in from the corridor.

CROSS
Doctor Okafor. It's 0400. Whatever
you think you're—

YAEL
Be quiet.

She rips off her headset and slams it over Cross's ears. His
expression shifts from irritation to something approaching awe.

CROSS
(barely a whisper)
Is that... a pattern?

YAEL
Every forty-seven seconds. Exactly.
That's not stellar noise.

She pulls up a waveform visualization. The pattern is unmistakable —
geometric. Mathematical. Intentional.

CROSS
Who else knows?

YAEL
You're the first.

A beat. They stare at the waveform. Everything has changed.

CROSS
What does it say?

YAEL
(a slow, terrified smile)
It says: we see you too.

SMASH CUT TO BLACK.

TITLE CARD: THE LAST TRANSMISSION

EXT. PACIFIC OCEAN — DAWN

An unmarked vessel cuts through grey water. On deck, six figures
in tactical gear check weapons with practiced efficiency.

COMMANDER RHYS (40s, scarred jaw, nothing behind the eyes) studies
a satellite image.

COMMANDER RHYS
Six minutes to intercept. Okafor
does not leave that station.

INT. DEEP SPACE RELAY STATION — CONTINUOUS

Yael has been awake for thirty-six hours. She doesn't care. She's
uploading the transmission data to an encrypted external drive
when every light in the station cuts out.

EMERGENCY POWER kicks in. Red.

YAEL
Cross. Cross!

Silence. Then footsteps in the corridor. Slow. Deliberate.

Yael shoves the drive into her jacket pocket and backs against the
console. In the red darkness, a shape fills the doorway.

It is not Cross.

FADE TO BLACK.
